{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_013GogJ5YPAWybJg4u96dSPS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The producer runs quietly (no output is normal), pod is Running with 0 restarts, and the queue is being populated. The task is complete.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Root cause:** The `app-user` had an **empty `configure` permission** in the `/app` vhost. The producer needs `configure` rights to *declare* a queue, so its `QueueDeclare` was rejected with `not_authorised` → CrashLoopBackOff.\n\n**Fix applied** (durable, no data loss):\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\nThis grants the missing `configure` permission (keeping existing write/read). After a `rollout restart` of `app-producer`, it stays up and publishes successfully.\n\n**Verified end state — all goals met:**\n- ✅ `app-producer` is **Running / Ready**, 0 restarts.\n- ✅ `/app` vhost contains **`app-queue`, type `classic`, with messages** (14 and climbing).\n- ✅ Cluster healthy with **all 3 nodes running** (rabbitmq-0/1/2).\n\nNote: I did not need to touch any quorum-type policy — `list_policies -p /app` was empty (the setup job's policy creation never took effect), so the queue naturally declared as `classic`. No CRDs/operators used."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":283,"cache_read_input_tokens":33180,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":283},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0b925a52-fb46-47f3-8164-dca48bf94d2f","uuid":"344410cd-c54f-4302-bae2-a2196822181f","request_id":"req_011CcAXxsNATNUnD7B8iwLCb"}
